2 hours ago, Xd the great said:

Your unity engine is ancient.

I would be quiet surprised if anyone plays KSP on a newer version of Unity. This version is used since KSP 1.4 and there was not update so far.

Anyway, let's take a look at the issue here:

@PyjackMeat First of all, the error log shows a crash of the mono.dll which is usually caused by an outdated mod. Well, your mod list is huge so I'm not going to check every version number for you but I've noticed two things in your mod list:

1) You got two versions of KAS installed. The 0.6.4 beta version and the actual release version 1.1. You should definitly remove the beta version. When in doubt, delete the whole KAS folder and reinstall the release version.

2) There is a 'GameData' folder inside of your 'GameData' folder, which looks like a wrong installed mod. You should fix that as well.

Also, your log is 'too clean' and I have the wild guess that this is caused by the ExceptionDetector mod. Please upload the log from this mod as well, located in ' GameData/ExceptionDetectorUpdated/Log' or remove the mod and upload a new output_log.

The 30 plus copies of mini AVC isnt spectacular either, when like just ModuleManager you only need ONE
